      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHE'S A DAME (6) went close at Gosford and Kembla Grange before a solid effort over 1600m at Newcastle, where she met some trouble late. Has the inside barrier today, and she positions forward. Will peak for this and is the one to beat. DERRY CITY FELIX (1) is also ready to win and can threaten, building on his half-length defeat over 1500m at Hawkesbury, where he jumped an equal favourite. Maps for a soft run and can make amends. PROPANE (5) just missed over 1300m at Newcastle and will be better for it. Has the winkers on for the first time and gives every indication that the 1600m will suit. Won't have to improve much to feature. CRISPY LEAVES (7) is also third-up out of the same contest, where he ran on late, beaten 2.7L. COL DU TOURMALET (4) debuts and brings two 1200m trial wins from Warwick Farm. Interesting kicking off over this trip, but he clearly has good ability and will get every chance. The betting will be key.",
